— 1. Formam dii perduint. Inallusion to sables, in which men from the violence of grief, anger, or love, lay aside the human form aud assume another. Amphitryon intimates that Sosia shall suffer pun- ishment, unless suddenly changed by the power of the gods.

— 2. Saturni hostia. 73. 10. Accipe. Mercury is here supposed to suit the action to the word, by easting water upon the head of Amphitryon.
